CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 7, 1941, pg. 18 reads: "Central Baptist Fetes Its Youthful Pastor And Wife" - Words of praise and commendation flowed like water and were as plentiful as the delicious chicken a la king at the banquet Monday night in Central Baptist Church for the Rev. and Mrs. Cornell E. Talley...Bottom center: W. E.Tinker presents smiling Mrs. Talley and Rev. Talley with one of numerous gifts they received. Mrs. Tinker is seated to Rev. Talley's left.  Mrs. W.D. Battle to Mrs. Talley's right...Staff photos by Harris"
TitMainTitle: Martha Talley holding large gift, and Rev. Cornell E. Talley standing behind table, flanked by Mrs. W.D. Battle on left, and Mrs. Tinker on right, in Central Baptist Church with "Welcome" fringed banner, for banquet honoring Talley
